default‘...judicial review provides a prompt and efficient remedy for many persons affected by government action in large numbers of cases, often of critical importance to them, which are conceded by public bodies at an early s
defaulttage, and at little cost either to the public body or the legal aid fund. By ensuring that officials are accountable to the law, judicial review provides a powerful corrective to poor decision making, the importance of which goes well beyond the relatively
default small number of cases which get near a court. We consider that the proposals in the Consultation Paper will undermine the accountability of public bodies to the detriment of society as a whole and the vulnerable in particular’
default.
default&#xa0;default     default The NAYJ fully agrees with this view and believes it encapsulates the negative impact this will 
default      have on access to justice and erosion of human rights.
